<h1>Case 11 — City Post Office Control System</h1>

<h2>Brief Description</h2>
<p>
The City Post Office Control System automates parcel sorting, tracking, delivery route planning, 
and priority-based dispatching. It ensures efficient citywide logistics and reduces delivery delays 
through smart routing and systematic handling.
</p>

<h2>Rising Problems</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Slow sorting of parcels due to manual handling.</li>
    <li>Misrouted or lost parcels because of poor record management.</li>
    <li>Urgent parcels not given priority during high workload periods.</li>
    <li>Inefficient delivery routes increasing fuel usage and delays.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Solutions / Logic Used</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Hash Tables:</strong> Store sender/receiver details and parcel tracking IDs for fast lookup.</li>
    <li><strong>Queue:</strong> Used for regular (non-urgent) parcel sorting and processing.</li>
    <li><strong>Priority Queue (Heap):</strong> Ensures urgent parcels are dispatched first.</li>
    <li><strong>Dijkstra’s Algorithm:</strong> Calculates the shortest and fastest delivery routes across Velora.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Suitable SDGs</h2>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 9 — Industry, Innovation & Infrastructure</strong>
    <p>Improves logistics infrastructure using smart routing and digital parcel systems.</p>
</div>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 11 — Sustainable Cities & Communities</strong>
    <p>Enhances city services by ensuring timely delivery and reducing operational inefficiencies.</p>
</div>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 12 — Responsible Consumption & Production</strong>
    <p>Optimizes resource usage, minimizes wasted trips, and improves workflow efficiency.</p>
</div>

